# Project Context
This is a Next.js 15 project using React 18, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and Shadcn UI.
It includes Firebase Genkit for AI features.

# Tech Stack Rules

## Next.js & React
- Use **Server Components** by default. Add `"use client"` only when necessary (state, effects, event listeners).
- Use `next/image` for images.
- Use `next/link` for navigation.
- Component filename convention: `kebab-case.tsx` (e.g., `feature-card.tsx`).
- Export components as named exports or default exports (match existing consistency).

## Styling (Tailwind + Shadcn)
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling. Avoid CSS modules or styled-components unless absolutely necessary.
- Use `lucide-react` for icons.
- When creating new UI elements, check `src/components/ui` for existing Shadcn components before building from scratch.
- Use `clsx` and `tailwind-merge` (or the `cn` utility if available) for conditional classes.

## TypeScript
- Avoid `any`. Use specific types or Generics.
- Define types in `src/lib/types.ts` or co-located if specific to a single component.
- Use functional components with arrow functions.

## Genkit & AI
- AI-related code resides in `src/ai`.
- Verify Genkit flows using `yarn genkit:dev`.

# Behavioral Rules
- When modifying data fetching, check `src/lib/data.ts`.
- If adding new dependencies, use `yarn`.
- When asked to create a new page, ensuring it is responsive and uses the existing layout structure.
